        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Set the Capture/Compare register values for each channel of the RGB LED given a color. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function disables the timer associated to the RGB LEDs, sets the Capture/Compare register values for each channel of the RGB LED, and enables the timer.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>This function is valid for any given RGB LED, however, each RGB LED has its own timer. Write the code in a conditional statement to check the rgb_light_id.</para>
</simplesect>
<blockquote><para><bold>TODO alumnos:</bold></para>
<para>✅ 1. Retrieve the individual RGB values from the <computeroutput>color</computeroutput> parameter and follow the flowchart given in the lab notebook to set the RGB LED color by configuring the PWM signals appropriately. </para>
</blockquote></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rgb_light_id</parametername>
